pokedexEntries.red: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
pokedexEntries.blue: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration, it lost its sense of smell.
pokedexEntries.gold: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates, making the stench around them worse.
pokedexEntries.silver: Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.
pokedexEntries.crystal: As it moves, a very strong poison leaks from it, making the ground there barren for three years.
pokedexEntries.ruby: From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: This Pokémon's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, Muk are certain to gather.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It prefers warm and humid habitats. In the summertime, the toxic substances in its body intensify, making Muk reek like putrid kitchen garbage.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
pokedexEntries.diamond: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

pokedexEntries.black2: It's so stinky! Muk's body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: This Pokémon's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, Muk are certain to gather.
pokedexEntries.sun: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that's a good thing.
pokedexEntries.moon: After recent environmental improvements, this Pokémon is now hardly seen at all. People speculate that it may go extinct at some point.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they’ve long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.
